place.name: Casa cu Cerb
place.description:
Casa cu Cerb is set in one of the oldest buildings in Sighisoara, named after the mural of a stag adorning the facade. It is 111 m from the Clock Tower and 100 m from Museum Square.

The rooms are located on the 2nd floor or attic level, and they come with free WiFi, satellite TV, telephone, wooden floors, and a private bathroom.

Guests can enjoy their meals in the on-site restaurant, serving traditional Romanian and international dishes. A cafe is 50 m away.

Sighisoara Train Station is 1.2 mi from Casa cu Cerb. Private parking is available in the lower town, outside the citadel, 500 m away, for a surcharge.

place.name: Sandalandala
place.description: If you have a tent, you're near the Black Sea, maybe in Romania, maybe not too far, Sandalandala Camping is the place you'll wanna be. Sandalandala is a brand new camping in Vama Veche, with enough room for 400 tents, free wi-fi, hot water showers 24/7, a bar that's open 'till the break of dawn, lovely music and an interesting terrace. And the beach is only 100 meters from the camping.
